ull},{"portName":"Chaguarama","displayOrder":5,"co2":622.333599999999900000,"eeoi":4.660048531976015000,"aer":3.542345353372446000,"soxMt":1.984400000000000200,"sox":0.014859233547494797,"noxMt":19.980000000000004000,"nox":0.149610706651353600,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Paranagua","displayOrder":4,"co2":314.242199999999970000,"eeoi":7.627037561780536000,"aer":5.797708088570922000,"soxMt":0.949400000000000000,"sox":0.023043084159780076,"noxMt":10.070000000000000000,"nox":0.244411056971756220,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Beaumont","displayOrder":2,"co2":141.987600000000000000,"eeoi":6.145585180055401000,"aer":4.671579052652635500,"soxMt":0.120000000000000000,"sox":0.005193905817174515,"noxMt":4.439999999999999500,"nox":0.192174515235457030,"euEtsDetails":null}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2023-01-06T16:38:12.907","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"\u2022\tPre-calc:               $42,026 x 29.6 days = $356,332\n\n\u2022\tEarnings:              $25,558 x 47.4 days = ($210,461)\nDifference:    Final earnings may look daunting, however this includes ballasting her to Trinidad for redelivery.  Taking this into account, the expense to redeliver was $571k considering time/bunkers.  Initially generated 1:1, chrts added Salvador as a disport which increased the freight to $23.10/ton.  With overage and new rate, freight was billed $240k higher than originally anticipated.  Additionally 2.6 days of demurrage increased earnings by $80k.  On her laden passage she ended up performing pretty efficiently and saved 1.8mt/day.  Given the extended days due to the added disport, she actually consumed about the same as if calling only 1.\nIf we were to compare apples to apples, (open Brazil/no redelivery), final earnings would have been $44,281 x 34 days = 486,160.  Also important to note, even with the cost to redeliver, her YTD earnings are 2.4m.\nImprovements:  None to note\n\nFIXTURE NOTE\nLargo sun opened Ecmex much earlier than anticipated unfortunately on Saturday after a PMI run hence hitting the spot market while it was on the way down, falling fast and with a very heavily populated position list. Hence on Monday morning we took out the first cargo we saw as competing with about 17 prompt vessels, Ipiranga usg brazil at ws245 off her dates which in the big picture is less than last however next done was ws230 then went as low as ws220 which is currently being repeated still by many vessels. She is making a profit open Paranagua, however if we ballast her back up to Pont lisas for redelivery it should be around 25kpd or (200k loss PnL) Bss 30kpd to redel. To note PnL on the ecmex run was around 920k give or take some, which amounts to around 700k ish pnl profits on the extension (latest redel 30 SEP in cbs). For ref, usg-cbs at 675k L/S which was done same day on later dates would have been approx. 250k\u002B loss open Pozos."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-10-04T19:46:02.22","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"diff. in bunkers delivery vs redelivery (same price both ends)"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-09-30T00:23:41.32","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"updated eta to trinidad"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-09-09T13:55:48.357","modifiedByFull":"Butcher, Carol","remark":"updated to include overage"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-09-02T13:37:16.733","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"updated to include Salvador"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-19T13:25:14.47","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"Updated to include redelivery ballast leg to Trindad"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}